flowchart TB
    M["MASTER CLAIM<br><br>I build production-shaped ML platforms and MLOps systems end to end — from the governed data world they depend on, to the runtime and learning paths they operate through, to the controls, evidence, and operating discipline required to run them under pressure.<br><br>The fraud platform is the proof surface for that claim."] --> S1["1. SOLVE THE WORLD FIRST<br><br>I did not begin with a model or a thin pipeline. I began by building the world the platform would have to survive: a layered synthetic fraud engine that constructs merchant geography and demand, entities/accounts/devices, legitimate behaviour, fraud campaigns, labels, and case chronology with deterministic lineage and PASS/no-read legitimacy before anything becomes consumable downstream."]
    S1 --> S2["2. TURN IT INTO ONE SHARED OPERATING WORLD<br><br>I used that engine to create one replayable three-month fraud world that runtime replay, stress, supervision, case history, and later ML all share. The accepted current slice carries 331.5M events, backed by a 473.4M-event raw horizon, so the whole platform works against one governed truth path instead of disconnected toy datasets."]
    S2 --> S3["3. BUILD THE REAL PLATFORM<br><br>On top of that world, I built a production-shaped AWS ML platform across ingress/admission, event transport, real-time decisioning, action/output handling, case and label operations, governed learning and release, and governance/meta surfaces that can reconstruct and defend what happened."]
    S3 --> S4["4. EARN BOUNDED PRODUCTION READINESS<br><br>I did not stop at wiring. I took the platform through bounded production readiness: integrated full-platform proof closed at ~3049.811 steady / 6188 burst / 3019 recovery EPS, then widened stress authorization held over 2.36M admitted events at ~3007 steady / 6359 burst / 3017 recovery, while semantic continuity remained intact across runtime, case/label, learning, and ops paths."]
    S4 --> S5["5. CLOSE THE GOVERNED MLOps CORRIDOR<br><br>Runtime, label, and case truth became point-in-time-correct learning data on managed surfaces; train/eval became governed; candidate publication and rollback had to be real; and active runtime model authority stayed tied back to governed learning truth rather than drifting away from it."]
    S5 --> S6["6. MAKE IT OPERABLE, CHALLENGEABLE, AND COST-REAL<br><br>Readiness had to mean more than green dashboards: alerts, runbooks, exact run reconstruction, audit-grade evidence readback, day-2 operator surfaces, safe idle/restore controls, and spend tied to proof or risk retired all became part of the engineering claim."]
    S6 --> S7@{ label: "7. CURRENT PHASE: CAPSTONE OPERATING MISSION<br><br>The hard threshold has already been crossed. The current layer is not 'can the platform be built?' but 'can the already-ready system be run, challenged, changed, recovered, audited, and defended like a real production ML Platform / MLOps system?' That is what the live replay/load/incident/change/audit phase exists to prove." }
